guish between interstellar ice photochemistry and warm surface chemistry as separate environmental contexts.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P7\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_011\": 0.63\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.69,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.78,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.51,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.12,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.53,\n      \"feedback\": \"This is a coherent near-miss pathway, accurately reflecting literature that UV photolysis can generate diaminohexanoic acid isomers with lysine's formula but not confirmed lysine. It is not target-achieving, but it is a good representation of one of the closest known abiotic approaches to lysine-like composition.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Keep this branch explicitly labeled as a compositional analog route, not lysine synthesis.\",\n        \"Consider assigning a distinct environmental label if modeling cold UV ice chemistry rather than general surface conditions.\",\n        \"Note analytical ambiguity and coelution issues discussed in the literature.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_005\": 0.78,\n        \"rxn_012\": 0.71\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.75,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.8,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.67,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.16,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.62,\n      \"feedback\": \"This surrogate pathway is one of the better parts of the network. Diaminopropionic acid is a well-supported prebiotic lysine surrogate in the literature, and the network appropriately uses it to reflect how early systems might compensate for lysine's absence. The weakness is that the chemistry from generic HCN + NH3 to Dpr is oversimplified relative to the more specific dehydroalanine nitrile/ammonia chemistry reported by Thoma and Powner.\